The paper proposes a new language model that is designed for text editing and rewriting tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the natural language processing (NLP) sub-category of computer science (cs.CL). The model is also trained using a lower bound of the marginal data likelihood, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions experiments on style transfer and damaged ancient text restoration, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
